Has nice features, however the actual emulation is hit or miss. Some games that I tried would freeze up, while multi-language roms would display Japanese text, and there is no option in the emulator settings to select the bios region in order to get the games to show English instead. Also no SMS support so far as I know, which seems like it should have been an obvious inclusion, especially since many games have a better SMS version due simply to the higher resolution.
Great app allowing me to relive all the classic Game Gear games I played as a kid.

Solid working Game Gear emulator. Plays every game I throw at it. Bluetooth controller support is solid. I use a Gamesir g3s and I don't notice any input lag; it's very responsive.  The controller of course had to be properly mapped. Also comes with a nice amount of features such as rewinding/fast forwarding, quick save/load, and also plays games from your SD card which is very important. Terrific emulator; plays games in excellent quality. Easily 5/5 stars. I highly recommend it. I'm using a Snapdragon S7 Edge for reference.
